explanation: The code snippet demonstrates proper resource management and error handling. It allocates cryptographic resources (RNG and skcipher) and registers a key type. In case of any failure during these operations, it correctly jumps to cleanup labels (error_cipher, error_rng) to free any resources that were successfully allocated up to that point, preventing memory leaks. The use of goto statements for cleanup is a standard and accepted pattern in the Linux kernel for managing resource lifetimes.
